### Learnings
- The feature was implemented prior to this agent run. All acceptance criteria were already satisfied. The task was to verify correctness and gate-pass.
- The spec.md guard pattern (try `fs.access` → catch → create) matches the same pattern used for all other generated files (`protolab.config`, `CLAUDE.md`, `proto.config.yaml`).

### Notes for Developer
- spec.md is only generated when `research` data is available in the POST body. The client UI must call `/api/setup/research` first, then pass the result to `/api/setup/project`.
- The "does not overwrite" guarantee is implemented via `fs.access` — if the file is accessible, it pushes `'spec.md (already exists)'` to `filesCreated` and skips generation.

